# OpenClaw Architecture & System Rules

## 1. Core Stack
- Execution/Analyst: Strict C++17 optimized for ultra-low latency. 
- Monitors/Scouts: Python 3.11.
- Infrastructure: Docker Compose, Traefik reverse proxy.

## 2. The Design Contract (DO NOT VIOLATE)
- RULE-009: Every container must hard-abort at startup with [FATAL] if any required environment variable is missing. No silent defaults.
- RULE-015: AI models NEVER determine trade size, side, or price. Only deterministic C++ handles this via the Half-Kelly Criterion.
- RULE-018: Zero-share Kelly results are hard-blocked. Do not force a 1-share minimum purchase.

## 3. Data Integrity
- When interacting with `memory_bank.db`, you must respect strict SQLite thread-locking rules.
- Do not modify `RegimeStateMachine.hpp` without explicit approval, as it breaks synchronization with the Monte Carlo Permutation Tests.